    <!--Help-->
    <string name="help_planANewRouteTitle">PLANNING A NEW ROUTE</string>
    <string name="help_planANewRouteText">
        If you want to plan a new route, you can use the "Plan a New Route" button on the main menu.
        Here, you can select the destinations you want to travel to. Once this is done, you can start
        your route using the "Start Route" button. Alternatively, you can save your new route,
        using the button in the top right of the screen. You will then be prompted to enter a name
        for your new route. Enter a name, click save, and you will be presented with your saved routes.
    </string>

    <string name="help_myRoutesTitle">USING SAVED ROUTES</string>
    <string name="help_myRoutesText">
        From this screen, you can start one of your saved routes. This is a good idea, if for example,
        you routinely travel from your home to an ATM then a convenience store. All you need to do,
        is tap on the route you would like to start, and you will be brought to the map screen.
    </string>

    <string name="help_preferencesTitle">SETTING YOUR PREFERENCES</string>
    <string name="help_preferencesText">
        If you would like to save a custom location, you can do so in the "Set My Preferences" screen.
        ***FINISH THIS***
    </string>

    <string name="help_walkingDistanceTitle">SETTING YOUR WALKING DISTANCE </string>
    <string name="help_walkingDistanceText">
        Here, you can set your preferred walking distance. If this is not set, a default of five(5)
        kilometres(km) will be used.
    </string>
